## Latitude and Biodiversity


3.  下面哪个句子最好地表达了文章中高亮句子的基本信息?
The tropics contain a larger surface area of land than higher latitudes—a fact that is not always evident 
when we examine commonly used projections of Earth’s curved surface, since this tends to exaggerate the areas
of land in the higher latitudes—and some biogeographers regard the differences in diversity as a reflection of this effect. 
错因：未理解表因果关系的since this tends to exaggerate the areas of land in the higher latitudes

4.Why does the author mention “Klaus Rohde” in the passage?
Although area may contribute to biodiversity, it is certainly not the whole story; otherwise, large landmasses would always be richer in species.
错因：只对应了does not, 未对应句意

7.Paragraph 3 mentions which of the following as creating the structural complexity of a forest?
 错因：为抓住关键词 forest

